  <rte>
    <name>Yewbarrow from Wasdale</name>
    <desc>This Lake District walk is short, full of interest and if you only have time for one walk in Wasdale this is a must. It provides great views all the way round, has some scrambling and a short section of ridge walking.</desc>
    <author>Copyright Walking Britain</author>
	<url>www.walkingbritain.co.uk/walk-1176-description</url>
